erische Unfähigkeit, sondern als Produkt bewusster Bestrebungen zur Konsolidierung einer eigenen Gattungstradition und Überwindung ihres prekären Status, an denen intertextuelle Verfahren zentral Anteil haben.  aThis differentiated analysis of the Sangspruch verses by Der Kanzler, a poet of the late thirteenth century, shows that intertextuality is the central device used in the text production of Sangspruchdichtung, which responds to its precarious status as a genre: its verses reference more prestigious texts that are alien to the genre in order to participate in their authority while consolidating their own tradition by alluding to other Sangsprüche.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Apr 2021) 4aDer Kanzler. 4aIntertextualität. 4aSangspruchdichtung.  aIntertextualität Sangspruchdichtung.  aSangspruchdichtung.  aintertextuality.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package 2021z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z978311075377608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU0 cEPUBz97831107129640 cprintz978311071285840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311071288940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110712889423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110712889.jpg  a978-3-11-075070-6  DG Ebook Package 2021b2021  aZDB-23-DGGb2021  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DKUb2021